reviews.text: Super friendly staff!! It was a bit of a wait to get in but worth it! This place does good for these cats. And I love how they had people coming to do adopt. Great place doing great things. Anyone looking for a kitten/cat to adopt, the staff will help and answer you questions. I came from Florida for they day and can't wait to come back again. I also took a few pics I'd love to share:]

Stopped in here for a 30-minute visit (reserved online) because I'm thinking about adopting a cat. The staff is friendly and the cats are wonderfully social! The cost is also reasonable. My only complaint was that it smelled a little bit, but with all the upholstered furniture that would be hard to avoid. Will definitely consider adopting from here.

This place was nice! A table to color at, couches and chairs, a bathroom, a turtle tank, and cat toys. They also have a little snack bar as well as tea and coffee. The cats were super friendly and cute. I recommend going early in the day if you want the cats to be more playful and less tired though. They also had rats, Emile and Remy. The people were very welcoming and respectful.

To be honest I just came for the kitties (not the coffee) and I wasn't disappointed - so many cats young and older ones and all so adorable. We played, we snuggled and relaxed - I loved every minute of the two hours I spent
There's lots of lovely cats what else could you want. Cost$7 per half hour. And although they take walk in the waiting list is long make a reservation if you plan on going

reviews.text: I am a regular here, and they very quickly leaned my order, and often start making it a soon as they see me walk in. The food is very good, too. Recommend the CC Salad!  My husband cannot results their excellent croissants, which I believe are made by one of the propietors definite the best coffee shop in the area.
Cute decor and good tea. Nice staff. Wish they had real cats roaming around! Will come back.
Full coffee bar and great coffee. Nice place to hang out for a couple hours on your laptop. They have good pastries. Staff is lackluster.

My first visit, early Saturday morning.   Nice music, warm atmosphere and local artist friendly (wall photos. Etc). I was offered a loyalty card and having reviewed the menu, will make this a regular stop, en route to work.  I wish the owners much success!

Such a cute place in ridgewood around a nice little semi-commercial area. Got a vanilla macchiato and loved it! It tasted really good and sitting down in the back gave me some time to review some notes at the same time. Great place to come sit down if you have to get some work done and enjoy the vibes of the place and people it attracts. The barista there the night I went also was super friendly and talked to almost every person who bought something and the conversations I was hearing from the back even drew me in. Also the sandwiches and foods there looked reallly good, definitely will be trying one my next time around! There’s tons of seating in the back too 
Tip: ask for a stamp card! Some places don’t give it out unless you ask, sadly didn’t, but wish I did so ask!
Also ask for the WiFi password !

reviews.text: Beverages and bakery items are top notch. However, the sandwich I bought wasn't impressive. The atmosphere is warm, quiet and cozy. The outdoor seating has a nice view of the town and the Hudson. A peaceful place to have coffee or tea with a danish. I'll definitely be back again.
Very good coffee.  Little pricey for food but good as well.  Simple dishes would work better.
Had a great breakfast burrito here, also, excellent coffee. Cash only, be warned. Cute, hip interior with nice comfy looking tables. Popular, so get there early for a seat. Free WiFi.
I ordered tea (chai) and it was not hot enough and way too sweet
Great coffee. My sandwich was delicious, the service was fantastic. The cafe has a great atmosphere and is the perfect place to hang out with friends.

reviews.text: This was a cool thing to do, and they take walk-ins which is nice. Their macaroons were delicious. But you can't pick up the cats, which I understand because they have so many people coming through at once that they probably get tired of it. I went to one in Philly and you could pick them up so I guess that's why I expected to be able to do that here.

Great experience, kids loved playing with kitties. The staff was pleasant and friendly. It's best if you can sign the waiver prior to your visit to expedite things. You can order some coffee and pastries and they can bring it to you from a cafe next door. There were 7-8 cats, most of them were asleep, but a couple of cats were active and curious, so the kids had a chance to play with them. Some reviewers were complaining about the odor in the place, but in fact the place is kept clean and organized. $16 for a child and an adult for 1 hour.

Fun, cute cat cafe. Didn't try any of the bakery treats, but they looked really good. Very clean place, and the cats seemed very happy and well taken care of. While it wasn't super busy, I would recommend making an appointment because the space is rather small.

Didn’t come here for the humans but the staff were nice and friendly lol.  Cats were friendly, approachable and interested in playing with people.  Cats were all types and sizes.  Great experience and def coming back.  Go early, didn’t need a reservation when it opened and the cats will be more likely to play and interested in playing with you then later in the day.
Great place. Cats are so cute. I felt other people were kind of hogging/bothering the cats. But the staff can't really help this too much.  Staff was really nice

reviews.text: This place is so adorable. This is my first Kitty cafe and definitely won't be my last. All the cats are well taken care of and available for adoption. The coffee and drinks are pretty good too. They've got two floors where you can play with the cats. Definitely worth a visit.

If you go early on a week day the wait shouldn't  be too bad. We called in advance and asked how busy they were beforehand which is always a good idea. We got there at 3:30 and the cats were being fed and getting a break until 4 so we got some lattes while we waited which were really good! Cats were really friendly and staff was too. Loved the fact that the cats have their own little closed off room in the back where they can get away from people if they want to 😂 All of them are up for adoption too which is wonderful

Great time! Definitely would go back. The cats are really cute, and there's a big selection of ways to interact with them. The staff are really fun to talk to as well, so make sure you ask them about the cats and stuff. Some of them are a bit grumpier than others so be a bit careful.

I was very excited about visiting this place after I saw an episode of “My cat from Hell”, and today, I must say it was really disappointing. After expending almost 40 bucks in coffee and pastries for 2, a rude lady told me that to visit the kitties I should have an appointment and must pay a $20 fee and limited to one hour. Visiting this place was one of my reasons for flying to NY, and I left very disappointed. 

Burnt coffee, good pastries, $20 extra each and appointment needed to hangout with the kitties 👎🏻😿😾

I didn't get any consumables, and the entry fee for the cat room seems steep ($20 per person--regardless of age or time spent), but the look on my daughter's face was worth it.  Food and drink are allowed in the cat rooms, and they offer adoption at a reasonable fee ($125).  All cats are spayed/neutered, and have had all of their shots.
